Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and set aside.

While the rice cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{390%g} and sliced pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) into the pan. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, @butter{15%g} and @water{50%ml}.

Stir to combine and simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}.

Add the cooked rice to the chicken pan and stir until everything's mixed together and piping hot.

Share the chicken jambalaya between your #bowls{}.

Top with a dollop of @soured cream{75%g} and drizzle with @honey{1%tsp}, then sprinkle with the spring onion to finish.

Enjoy!